Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce}(peeled and cut on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces). Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Honey{2%teaspoon}, and ½ tsp @Colman's English Mustard{1%tablespoon}. Taste and add more mustard if you'd prefer extra heat; set aside.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon}, @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. On empty side of same sheet, toss potatoes with a drizzle of oil, salt, pepper, and @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}. Roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 baking sheets; roast potatoes on top rack and carrots on middle rack.)

Meanwhile, place @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, lemon zest, and @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon} in a #gallon-size zip-close bag{}. Season with salt (we used 1 tsp; 2 tsp for 4 servings) and pepper.

Place @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} in a #medium bowl{}; add @Pork Cutlets{12%ounce} and turn to coat. Place coated pork in bag with panko mixture and seal to close. Shake until pork is evenly coated.

> TIP: You may need to move around cutlets in bag, pressing with your hands, to spread out panko and make it stick.

Heat a ¼-inch-layer of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added to pan, add pork. Cook until panko is golden and pork is cooked through, ~{2%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Divide pork, potatoes, and carrots between plates. Serve with creamy mustard sauce for dipping or drizzling over, and lemon wedges on the side.